{"aid": "http://arxiv.org/abs/2504.04894v1", "title": "Non-algebraic cobordisms between quasipositive knots", "summary": "We show that for every genus $g \geq 0$, there exist quasipositive knots
$K_0^g$ and $K_1^g$ such that there is an optimal cobordism of genus $g$
between $K_0^g$ and $K_1^g$, but there is no ribbon cobordism of genus $g$ in
either direction and thus no algebraic cobordism between these two knots. This
gives a negative answer to a question posed by Feller in 2016.", "main_category": "math.GT", "categories": "math.GT", "published": "2025-04-07T10:06:14Z"}
